commit.message:
brought in new stuff from John's branch?

This commit was intended to bring in John's final GUI changes, including adding clefs and new staff lines. Not ure if it worked...

apparent change to the treble clef image

The treble clef image seems to have changed, but I'm not sure why and the new one appears funky. I'm commiting this in case and we can roll back if needed.

Merge remote-tracking branch 'refs/remotes/origin/master'

Conflicts:
	GUI.py
	clf.py

fixed the double-wait issue

The listen method blocks to get data, but the GUI was still set up with a delay on its loop, causing missing data and slow performance.
Plotting frequency and time domain signals.
GUI no longer broken.  Matplotlib not displayed.
removed merge conflict markers from seralizer script

Small GUI tweak

I shifted the notes down half a bar to make everything properly algined.

I fixed the note vanishing bug.

The notes were being filtered out by same note checks. I reworked the algorithm to fix the issue.
Migrate plot library to object oriented model.

GUI tweaks

I fixed staff alginment issues and made it scale better (i.e. fixed John's HARDCODING! :P)
fixed list reversal bug and some indentation

First serialization test complete

Using a standalone serialization script and the pickle library, we recorded 4 keys' worth of training data for the learning algorithms for keys B3-D4 (plus a 0-key baseline).
